name: UDP-N-acetylglucosamine 2-epimerase (non-hydrolysing)
comment: This bacterial enzyme catalyses the reversible interconversion of UDP-GlcNAc and UDP-ManNAc. The latter is used in a variety of bacterial polysaccharide biosyntheses. cf. EC 3.2.1.183, UDP-N-acetylglucosamine 2-epimerase (hydrolysing).

pathways.ec00520: Amino sugar and nucleotide sugar metabolism
